Name: ovarian benign neoplasm
Definition: A female reproductive organ benign neoplasm that is located_in the ovary.

Name: oophoritis
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by inflammation of the ovary.

Name: ovarian dysfunction
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by irregular or absent ovulation.

Name: anovulation
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by the absence of ovulation.

Name: ovarian cyst
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by the presence of a fluid-filled sac and is located_in the ovary.

Name: ovarian hyperstimulation syndrome
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by cystic enlargement of the ovaries and a fluid shift from the intravascular to the third space and has_symptom abdominal pain

Name: premature ovarian failure
Definition: An ovarian disease where ovaries do not produce estrogen despite high levels of circulating gonadotropins in women under 40.

Name: ovarian stromal hyperthecosis
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by the presence of nests of luteinized theca cells scattered throughout the ovary

Name: obsolete metastatic neoplasm of urethra
Definition: An ovarian disease that is characterized by the presence of nests of luteinized theca cells scattered throughout the ovary
